2-2. geom_point()

pacman::p_load("ggplot2")

x <- c(20, 65, 39, 42, 30, 54, 58, 77)
y <- c(10, 32, 17, 29, 18, 43, 39, 54)

df <- data.frame(x = x, y = y)

ggplot(df, aes(x = x, y = y)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x = "X", y= "Y", title = ""))++            # x, y, Title   theme_bw() + 
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=20, hjust = 0.5))

Result! x y .

x <- c(20, 65, 39, 42, 30, 54, 58, 77)

#  cor()cor(x, y, method = "pearson")

[1] 0.9163436
#  (1)
r <- sum( (x - mean(x))*(y - mean(y)) )/(sqrt( sum((x - mean(x))^2) )*sqrt( sum((y - mean(y))^2) ))
r

[1] 0.9163436

3-1-1. corrplot()

  • Package corrplot corrplot() .
pacman::p_load("corrplot")

x <- c(20, 65, 39, 42, 30, 54, 58, 77)
y <- c(10, 32, 17, 29, 18, 43, 39, 54)
z <- c(100, 150, 102, 111, 126, 109, 134, 115)

df <- data.frame(x = x, y = y, z = z)
cor <- cor(df)
cor

          x         y         z
x 1.0000000 0.9163436 0.4891900
y 0.9163436 1.0000000 0.2787342
z 0.4891900 0.2787342 1.0000000
corrplot(cor,                   #           method = "shade",      #   
         addshade = "all",      #   
         type = "lower",        #   
         tl.col = "black",      #   
         tl.srt = 0,            #     
         addCoef.col = "red"    #  
         )
